I don’t want to keep a minimum balance in the account. How can I do that without attracting any non-maintenance charges?

It’s simple if you have a Digital Savings Account – Prime. If you do not wish to keep a minimum balance of Rs 5000 in your account, just do an SIP or RD for a minimum amount of Rs 2000. Non-Maintenance fee will not be levied.
What type of accounts can be opened online?
Accounts which can be opened online are Savings Account + Fixed Deposits. Set-up your account by following the simple steps and complete your application online itself.
How does the online account opening process work?

The entire process is simple and requires your Aadhaar and PAN details to start with. An OTP will be sent to your mobile number linked with Aadhaar number for proceeding ahead with the online deposit(s) account opening
What if I don’t have my Aadhaar or PAN number?
Provide your details online and we will connect with you for fixing up appointment with our representative to take the request further
How will I get my account details?
We will be providing your account details on the screen once you submit the entire details. It will be also sent to your email id and will be part of your welcome kit
How many accounts can I open with Aadhaar OTP?
You can open only 1 OTP based account with any bank in India. If you already have OTP based account with any other banks then you cannot open online account with RBL Bank.
How can I transfer amount into this account?

Fund your account immediately through payment gateway option provided on the screen once the account is opened.You can also add your RBL Bank account as a payee for doing NEFT/IMPS transfer through other bank’s digital platform.The funding needs to be done from an account where you are an account holder
Can I use my account immediately once it is opened?

Yes, visit our website www.rblbank.com and on-board yourself on our Internet Banking instantly using your Customer ID and PAN Number. View our new E-banking platform for the host of transactions and services you can avail of, e.g. – Create Fixed Deposits, Recurring Deposits, Transfer funds, Bill Pay, etc.Also, download RBL Bank MoBank App on your smartphone through Google Play Store / App Store / Windows Phone Store to have the convenience of on the go access to your account
How much money can I transfer into my new account?
You can credit a maximum up to Rs.100,000/- at the time of account opening or as part of initial funding for your Savings Account / Fixed Deposit booking
Are there any specific limitations/restrictions linked to my account opened with Aadhaar OTP?

As per guidelines, following are the key checks linked with accounts opened with Aadhaar OTP

- Aggregate balance in your accounts (including fixed deposits) to be within Rs.100,000/-
- Total amount of credit in a financial year to be within Rs.200,000/-
- In-person verification to be completed within 1 year of account opened
What is In-person verification and requirement related to it?

In order to operate your account without any limitations/restrictions we need to meet you in-person to collect copy of your KYC document and Signature to update in our records\n\nThe activity would require minimal documentations and needs to be completed within 1 year from date of account opening. The account requires to be closed if it is not completed within timelines as per guidelines
Can I transact or place a request through RBL Bank branches?

You can access services linked with our branch network post completion of In-person verification process. Till such you can place all relevant banking transactions or services by using our alternate banking facilities i.e. Retail Net Banking, MoBank App, Debit Card, SMS Banking, Phone Banking
What will be the content of my welcome KIT?

The Welcome Kit shall carry your Welcome Letter, Debit Card linked to your Digital Savings Account, BCSBI Code Copy and Passbook. A cheque book will be issued automatically once you successfully complete your In Person Verification process.
How can I generate the PIN for my debit card?
Generate from Bank service Section in this app, You will get option to generate
My name and address details updated on Aadhaar Card is incorrect. Will I be able to update it correctly in bank records while opening the digital savings account?
No, the details would be captured as it is from the Aadhaar Card database and hence the same cannot be rectified while opening the digital savings account
What happens to my account if the limitations / restrictions for usage of digital savings account are breached?

If the balance in the digital savings account exceeds Rs.1 lakh in a given day or cumulative credit values exceed Rs.2 lakh in a financial year or In-person verification is not completed within 1 year of account being opened, the bank reserves the right to put the account on a total freeze, till such time that customer completes the full KYC process
If I complete my full KYC, will the restrictions of Rs total balance of Rs 1 lac and total cumulative credits of Rs 2 lac will still be applicable?
No, once you complete your full KYC these restrictions are withdrawn. You can enjoy an extended account balance of more than Rs 1 lakh cumulative deposit of more than 2 lakhs in a financial year.
